{
 "poems": [
  {
   "id": "where-light-never-goes",
   "title": "Where light never goes",
   "page": 1,
   "stanzas": [
    {
     "id": "where-light-never-goes-s1",
     "lines": [
      "Motherless baby",
      "Fatherless son",
      "A spark in the void",
      "Where once there was none"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "where-light-never-goes-s2",
     "lines": [
      "I needed a King",
      "I needed a Queen",
      "To call off the war",
      "Inside of my being"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "where-light-never-goes-s3",
     "lines": [
      "I needed a truce",
      "To this horrible war",
      "For the battles that raged",
      "Outside my front door"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "where-light-never-goes-s4",
     "lines": [
      "I am weary and worn",
      "From the war that’s within",
      "From the countless long battles",
      "I could so rarely win"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "where-light-never-goes-s5",
     "lines": [
      "I’ve toiled on for eons",
      "And eons again",
      "Being cut down and born",
      "Being born and then dead"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "where-light-never-goes-s6",
     "lines": [
      "Why would I choose",
      "A life of neglect?",
      "Of hoping and wishing",
      "Parallel lines intersect"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "where-light-never-goes-s7",
     "lines": [
      "A life with no hope",
      "A life of such lack",
      "A life I was given",
      "But I could never give back"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "where-light-never-goes-s8",
     "lines": [
      "Motherless baby",
      "Fatherless son",
      "A love came to be",
      "Where once there was none"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "where-light-never-goes-s9",
     "lines": [
      "A love came to be",
      "From a life of neglect",
      "From the dark came a spark",
      "From the twigs … came a nest!"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "where-light-never-goes-s10",
     "lines": [
      "So love in the Universe",
      "Is thus not conserved!",
      "From pure darkness came light",
      "From the egg … came a bird!"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "where-light-never-goes-s11",
     "lines": [
      "A bird that descended",
      "From great lizards that ended",
      "When huge meteors had rained",
      "And great floods swept away"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "where-light-never-goes-s12",
     "lines": [
      "The lizards that crawled",
      "Walking out of the sea",
      "And fought to persist",
      "With brain and with fist"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "where-light-never-goes-s13",
     "lines": [
      "For eons and eons",
      "Of life eating life",
      "An orgy of death",
      "And unending strife"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "where-light-never-goes-s14",
     "lines": [
      "Each eon a layer",
      "Of carnage and dread",
      "That was cut down by time",
      "And raised from the dead"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "where-light-never-goes-s15",
     "lines": [
      "This great churning of life",
      "That is seething in blood",
      "From the eons of rage",
      "And then drowned in the floods"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "where-light-never-goes-s16",
     "lines": [
      "From each layer of rock",
      "Made from lizards of old",
      "That were cut down by time",
      "And reduced into bones"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "where-light-never-goes-s17",
     "lines": [
      "In the rock, over eons",
      "A clear crystal grows",
      "From the bowels of darkness",
      "Where light never goes"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "where-light-never-goes-s18",
     "lines": [
      "I was desperate for light",
      "In the cold and the dark",
      "A hunger so painful",
      "The pain made a spark"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "where-light-never-goes-s19",
     "lines": [
      "A hunger so deep",
      "A hunger so wide",
      "I bed down for winter",
      "It was too cold outside"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "where-light-never-goes-s20",
     "lines": [
      "From inside that seething",
      "Mass of destruction",
      "Came crystals so ordered",
      "Light felt no obstruction"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "where-light-never-goes-s21",
     "lines": [
      "A crystal from chaos",
      "A crystal from rage",
      "Could channel the light",
      "Like a bow in the rain"
     ]
    }
   ]
  },
  {
   "id": "as-the-light-is-a-star",
   "title": "As the light is a star",
   "page": 5,
   "stanzas": [
    {
     "id": "as-the-light-is-a-star-s1",
     "lines": [
      "You thirst because",
      "You’re made of water",
      "And you love as a Son",
      "Who is loved by his Father"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "as-the-light-is-a-star-s2",
     "lines": [
      "For love has an",
      "Unbroken chain of command",
      "From atom to planet",
      "From brain to the hand"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "as-the-light-is-a-star-s3",
     "lines": [
      "Love is a force",
      "That loves all the same",
      "Love is a constant",
      "Putting gravity to shame"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "as-the-light-is-a-star-s4",
     "lines": [
      "Loving can increase",
      "By loving itself",
      "As ants gather sugar",
      "Calling more in to help"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "as-the-light-is-a-star-s5",
     "lines": [
      "Love gathers love",
      "To reap what it sows",
      "Love is the violin",
      "And also the bow"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "as-the-light-is-a-star-s6",
     "lines": [
      "Love is a name",
      "For something that’s felt",
      "Love’s the transaction",
      "And also the wealth"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "as-the-light-is-a-star-s7",
     "lines": [
      "Love’s the one thing",
      "That cannot be bought",
      "And love’s always free",
      "So it matters not"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "as-the-light-is-a-star-s8",
     "lines": [
      "Love is a word",
      "That was whispered and hushed",
      "For love slows the hurried",
      "When their progress is rushed"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "as-the-light-is-a-star-s9",
     "lines": [
      "Love shines a light",
      "On what love is not",
      "And brings back the memory",
      "Of things long forgot"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "as-the-light-is-a-star-s10",
     "lines": [
      "Love is the food",
      "That’s needed to live",
      "As food is the love",
      "The Great Mother will give"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "as-the-light-is-a-star-s11",
     "lines": [
      "Love can increase",
      "But never reduce",
      "Love’s never war",
      "But always the truce"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "as-the-light-is-a-star-s12",
     "lines": [
      "Love is coherent",
      "And love is dramatic",
      "Love is like music",
      "Rising up through the static"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "as-the-light-is-a-star-s13",
     "lines": [
      "Love is a feeling",
      "A feeling that stays",
      "A feeling you keep",
      "Past the last of your days"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "as-the-light-is-a-star-s14",
     "lines": [
      "Love you can keep",
      "For love’s what you *are*",
      "As the note is the music",
      "As the light is a star"
     ]
    }
   ]
  },
  {
   "id": "i-came-to-be-free",
   "title": "I came to be free",
   "page": 9,
   "stanzas": [
    {
     "id": "i-came-to-be-free-s1",
     "lines": [
      "I came to release",
      "To give in to peace",
      "To let be what will be",
      "To be truly, fully me"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "i-came-to-be-free-s2",
     "lines": [
      "I came to be free"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "i-came-to-be-free-s3",
     "lines": [
      "Freedom, they said",
      "Is earned, has a fee",
      "Is not up to you",
      "Is not up to me"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "i-came-to-be-free-s4",
     "lines": [
      "Freedom, they said",
      "May not come till you’re dead",
      "May not be in the cards",
      "So you’d best get ahead"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "i-came-to-be-free-s5",
     "lines": [
      "So I came to be free",
      "And deny them their fee",
      "I say *no* to their race",
      "I say *no* to their face"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "i-came-to-be-free-s6",
     "lines": [
      "Then you said to forgive",
      "All the ones who betrayed me",
      "And let go of the ropes",
      "I was whipped by when they shamed me"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "i-came-to-be-free-s7",
     "lines": [
      "You said to forgive",
      "Is how one learns to live",
      "In a world full of pain",
      "Full of heartache and shame"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "i-came-to-be-free-s8",
     "lines": [
      "To forgive is divine",
      "As the old saying said",
      "And divine is within",
      "Round your heart, not your head"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "i-came-to-be-free-s9",
     "lines": [
      "You learn to forgive",
      "By forgiving yourself",
      "For losing your faith",
      "In a world full of doubt"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "i-came-to-be-free-s10",
     "lines": [
      "You must learn to forgive",
      "Every moment you strayed",
      "From the safety of home",
      "When you’d lost your way"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "i-came-to-be-free-s11",
     "lines": [
      "All the love you prevented",
      "From enriching your life",
      "You became so accustomed",
      "To the grind, to the strife"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "i-came-to-be-free-s12",
     "lines": [
      "Forgive yourself",
      "For being the fish",
      "Who forgot about water",
      "Then for water you wished"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "i-came-to-be-free-s13",
     "lines": [
      "Forgive yourself",
      "For playing the game",
      "You forgot you were playing",
      "And the game, you became"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "i-came-to-be-free-s14",
     "lines": [
      "So dear, do you see",
      "Freedom does have a fee",
      "Forgiving yourself",
      "For forgetting you’re free"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "i-came-to-be-free-s15",
     "lines": [
      "You simply forgot",
      "And that’s really all",
      "So now just remember",
      "And your problem is solved"
     ]
    }
   ]
  },
  {
   "id": "volcano-in-a-sea-of-blue",
   "title": "Volcano in a sea of blue",
   "page": 13,
   "stanzas": [
    {
     "id": "volcano-in-a-sea-of-blue-s1",
     "lines": [
      "When I first saw you",
      "I saw fire in your eyes",
      "A volcano in the ocean",
      "A burning fire in a sea of blue"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "volcano-in-a-sea-of-blue-s2",
     "lines": [
      "I saw a warrior in you"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "volcano-in-a-sea-of-blue-s3",
     "lines": [
      "But battles make you weary",
      "I know",
      "And once one starts",
      "How long will it go?"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "volcano-in-a-sea-of-blue-s4",
     "lines": [
      "It takes one to know one",
      "And I’m a warrior too",
      "Will you take your armor off?",
      "And let me look at you?"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "volcano-in-a-sea-of-blue-s5",
     "lines": [
      "There now",
      "I see you",
      "And I want you even more"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "volcano-in-a-sea-of-blue-s6",
     "lines": [
      "I see you",
      "Raw and beautiful",
      "Some parts of you are sore"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "volcano-in-a-sea-of-blue-s7",
     "lines": [
      "Lay down, my warrior",
      "I have a gift for you",
      "A gift from me"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "volcano-in-a-sea-of-blue-s8",
     "lines": [
      "Here’s what I’ll do …"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "volcano-in-a-sea-of-blue-s9",
     "lines": [
      "Lay back",
      "My eyes",
      "Will hold your gaze"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "volcano-in-a-sea-of-blue-s10",
     "lines": [
      "Lay back",
      "Receive",
      "And be amazed"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "volcano-in-a-sea-of-blue-s11",
     "lines": [
      "Lay back",
      "Receive",
      "And hold my gaze"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "volcano-in-a-sea-of-blue-s12",
     "lines": [
      "This gift I give",
      "It’s all for you",
      "What comes next?",
      "What’s the next thing I should do?"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "volcano-in-a-sea-of-blue-s13",
     "lines": [
      "Lay back",
      "Receive",
      "It’s all for you"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "volcano-in-a-sea-of-blue-s14",
     "lines": [
      "Yes, volcano",
      "It’s time for you",
      "To release your lava",
      "Into my deep sea of blue"
     ]
    }
   ]
  },
  {
   "id": "god-of-choice",
   "title": "God of choice",
   "page": 17,
   "stanzas": [
    {
     "id": "god-of-choice-s1",
     "lines": [
      "As I watch in horror",
      "As I watch as you",
      "Are killing your people",
      "I don’t know what to do"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "god-of-choice-s2",
     "lines": [
      "I’ve watched as you make",
      "The gravest mistake",
      "As eons of rage",
      "March in throngs to your gates"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "god-of-choice-s3",
     "lines": [
      "And when you are questioned",
      "You always insist",
      "Your right to choose death",
      "To slaughter like this"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "god-of-choice-s4",
     "lines": [
      "To slaughter like this",
      "To slaughter like this",
      "You choose now to slaughter",
      "On this choice you insist"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "god-of-choice-s5",
     "lines": [
      "And if there is somewhere",
      "A god of free choice",
      "Who grants you the freedom",
      "To silence their voice"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "god-of-choice-s6",
     "lines": [
      "To slaughter the children",
      "On your patch of land",
      "For being born there",
      "And for what god they stand"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "god-of-choice-s7",
     "lines": [
      "But how can you though?",
      "For surely you know",
      "You’re forever connected",
      "To the seeds that you sow"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "god-of-choice-s8",
     "lines": [
      "Each mother that’s slaughtered",
      "Each child with no father",
      "Each family cut down",
      "Martyred sons, martyred daughters"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "god-of-choice-s9",
     "lines": [
      "And yet all the while",
      "You seem to insist",
      "It’s your right to kill them",
      "To slaughter like this"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "god-of-choice-s10",
     "lines": [
      "To slaughter like this",
      "To slaughter like this",
      "You insist on your right",
      "To put gun against fist"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "god-of-choice-s11",
     "lines": [
      "And if there is somewhere",
      "A god of free choice",
      "Who gives us our options",
      "And hears every voice"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "god-of-choice-s12",
     "lines": [
      "The god of all choices",
      "Must love you so much",
      "To stand by as you kidnap",
      "Our children from us"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "god-of-choice-s13",
     "lines": [
      "To watch as you slaughter",
      "his sons and his daughters",
      "his sisters and brothers",
      "his mothers and fathers"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "god-of-choice-s14",
     "lines": [
      "And surely our love",
      "For our little ones",
      "Is to God’s but a candle",
      "Held up to the sun"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "god-of-choice-s15",
     "lines": [
      "As we light a candle",
      "For each child you cut down",
      "They won’t be forgotten",
      "Even deep underground"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "god-of-choice-s16",
     "lines": [
      "They won’t be forgotten",
      "Because we can’t forget",
      "Each candle of life",
      "And a sun’s worth of death"
     ]
    }
   ]
  },
  {
   "id": "flower-of-winter",
   "title": "Flower of winter",
   "page": 21,
   "stanzas": [
    {
     "id": "flower-of-winter-s1",
     "lines": [
      "The flowers of spring",
      "Have dropped to the ground",
      "The leaves have descended",
      "And are scattered all around"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "flower-of-winter-s2",
     "lines": [
      "I mourn them, my flowers",
      "They retreat with the sun",
      "And are swallowed by soil",
      "For summer’s all done"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "flower-of-winter-s3",
     "lines": [
      "And rain soaks the earth",
      "As I shelter with fire",
      "And I dream of the sunlight",
      "Before summer retired"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "flower-of-winter-s4",
     "lines": [
      "Winter so cold",
      "No flowers dare bloom",
      "For the sun only glimmers",
      "Through great clouds of doom"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "flower-of-winter-s5",
     "lines": [
      "My hope fades away",
      "With each passing day",
      "My skin stings from cold",
      "And my eyes drip with rain"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "flower-of-winter-s6",
     "lines": [
      "Oh flowers of summer",
      "Oh roses of May",
      "The sun cannot warm you",
      "So you’ve gone away"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "flower-of-winter-s7",
     "lines": [
      "But flowers of winter",
      "Now spring from the ground",
      "The more cold and rain",
      "The more they abound"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "flower-of-winter-s8",
     "lines": [
      "Slimy and ugly",
      "Woodsy and clunky",
      "Fancy and delicate",
      "When it’s no longer sunny"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "flower-of-winter-s9",
     "lines": [
      "The flowers of winter",
      "Have sprung from the ground",
      "Like a great cast of players",
      "Who lay hid all around"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "flower-of-winter-s10",
     "lines": [
      "The great play of winter",
      "Bursting forth from the ground",
      "Under logs, under leaves",
      "They don’t need to be found"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "flower-of-winter-s11",
     "lines": [
      "Flowers of winter",
      "Springing up in the cold",
      "You grow from the remnants",
      "Of spring flowers grown old"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "flower-of-winter-s12",
     "lines": [
      "You make life of death",
      "Eating death to renew",
      "On old life you dine",
      "On dead flesh you chew"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "flower-of-winter-s13",
     "lines": [
      "One day I will die",
      "And my bones will be buried",
      "My body and spirit",
      "Will no longer be married"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "flower-of-winter-s14",
     "lines": [
      "With flowers of winter",
      "Encircling my frame",
      "I will sink underground",
      "To be earth once again"
     ]
    }
   ]
  },
  {
   "id": "gaman",
   "title": "Gaman!",
   "page": 25,
   "stanzas": [
    {
     "id": "gaman-s1",
     "lines": [
      "It can’t be real work",
      "If you don’t feel the grind",
      "It’s got to be painful",
      "Can’t let yourself slide"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "gaman-s2",
     "lines": [
      "“Gaman” is the strength",
      "As the Japanese say",
      "To put your nose on the stone",
      "And to grind it away"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "gaman-s3",
     "lines": [
      "So grind it I did",
      "Though once I did know",
      "The joy and the freedom",
      "Of feeling in flow"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "gaman-s4",
     "lines": [
      "Flow was a rhythm",
      "A music inside",
      "It smoothed out the edges",
      "Of pain in my life"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "gaman-s5",
     "lines": [
      "Flow my companion",
      "As dark as it seemed",
      "When I didn’t feel safe",
      "I could always daydream"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "gaman-s6",
     "lines": [
      "I’d dream of the person",
      "I needed to be",
      "To break from the bondage,",
      "Soar up, and fly free"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "gaman-s7",
     "lines": [
      "With jets on my feet",
      "And wings in my heart",
      "I dreamed of the day",
      "I could make a fresh start"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "gaman-s8",
     "lines": [
      "So hopeful I ran",
      "From a home full of pain",
      "And fled to the sea",
      "Trading snow for the rain"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "gaman-s9",
     "lines": [
      "On the shores of the land",
      "Where children had died",
      "I wept for myself",
      "To the ocean I cried …"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "gaman-s10",
     "lines": [
      "“Oh ocean, my ocean",
      "In waters so deep",
      "Beloved Earth Mother",
      "Hold my tears as I weep”"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "gaman-s11",
     "lines": [
      "To the ocean I cry",
      "“Don’t leave me to die",
      "Hear passion in me",
      "And come to my side”"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "gaman-s12",
     "lines": [
      "In my grief for a life",
      "I had lived with such hope",
      "I felt I was broken",
      "Like the butt of God’s joke"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "gaman-s13",
     "lines": [
      "My tears soaked the land",
      "As the tide lapped the sand",
      "And the ocean held space",
      "And the trees held my hand"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "gaman-s14",
     "lines": [
      "I cried for my father",
      "Under his father’s gun",
      "And I cried that I couldn’t",
      "Be the dutiful son"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "gaman-s15",
     "lines": [
      "I wept all the tears",
      "I had stopped long before",
      "When I couldn’t break down",
      "To a puddle on the floor"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "gaman-s16",
     "lines": [
      "But the ocean knows pain",
      "Sheds blood every day",
      "The waves create carnage",
      "And then wash it away"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "gaman-s17",
     "lines": [
      "The pain of the ocean",
      "To gulp children’s blood",
      "To drown a whole village",
      "In thousand-year floods"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "gaman-s18",
     "lines": [
      "The sea knows the pain",
      "Yet onward it flows",
      "Like breathing in tides",
      "And exhaling ghosts"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "gaman-s19",
     "lines": [
      "The sea can scream back",
      "As loud as you wish",
      "Can savagely end you",
      "Like sharks eat a fish"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "gaman-s20",
     "lines": [
      "Have I come here to die?",
      "Or to find some new growth?",
      "Could that be my choice?",
      "And can it be both?"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "gaman-s21",
     "lines": [
      "Because feeling those times",
      "When I wished I would die",
      "Feels like dying again",
      "And again the next time"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "gaman-s22",
     "lines": [
      "If healing is feeling",
      "And feeling’s like dying",
      "Then healing’s like killing",
      "The me that’s here crying"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "gaman-s23",
     "lines": [
      "A slaughter of me’s",
      "With my blood in the water",
      "Like seals being hunted",
      "By sharks they are slaughtered"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "gaman-s24",
     "lines": [
      "The slaughter of me’s",
      "Who I had to relive",
      "Every time I was slain",
      "And I had to forgive"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "gaman-s25",
     "lines": [
      "Forgive my belief",
      "That I could be so harmed",
      "By people and things",
      "To the point of alarm"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "gaman-s26",
     "lines": [
      "The waves are still breathing",
      "After eons of slaughter",
      "All the blood I can shed",
      "Just a drop in the water"
     ]
    }
   ]
  },
  {
   "id": "i-say-your-name",
   "title": "I say your name",
   "page": 31,
   "stanzas": [
    {
     "id": "i-say-your-name-s1",
     "lines": [
      "Son, my dear son",
      "My love, can you hear",
      "The sound of my whisper",
      "As I speak in your ear?"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "i-say-your-name-s2",
     "lines": [
      "I say your name",
      "In blades of grass",
      "In songs of birds",
      "In sunsets past"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "i-say-your-name-s3",
     "lines": [
      "I say your name",
      "My perfect son",
      "In fish swimming by",
      "In deer on the run"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "i-say-your-name-s4",
     "lines": [
      "I say your name",
      "With perfect love",
      "In songs of the crows",
      "And young mourning doves"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "i-say-your-name-s5",
     "lines": [
      "In great flocks of starlings",
      "In wind and in rain",
      "In all of these beings",
      "In all of these ways"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "i-say-your-name-s6",
     "lines": [
      "*I say your name*"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "i-say-your-name-s7",
     "lines": [
      "I call to you",
      "When you least expect",
      "My wind on your cheek",
      "A bug on your neck"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "i-say-your-name-s8",
     "lines": [
      "I say your name",
      "With morning dew",
      "I say your name",
      "In shades of blue"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "i-say-your-name-s9",
     "lines": [
      "*I do this all for you*"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "i-say-your-name-s10",
     "lines": [
      "And if, my son",
      "You heed my call",
      "I’ll send more signs",
      "I’ll send them all"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "i-say-your-name-s11",
     "lines": [
      "For nothing is",
      "A greater joy",
      "Than to be heard",
      "By my perfect boy"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "i-say-your-name-s12",
     "lines": [
      "I call to you",
      "In times of need",
      "And in my call",
      "I plant a seed"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "i-say-your-name-s13",
     "lines": [
      "A seed of love",
      "A love that’s free",
      "A love that grows",
      "A heart-shaped tree"
     ]
    }
   ]
  },
  {
   "id": "the-nutshell",
   "title": "The nutshell",
   "page": 33,
   "stanzas": [
    {
     "id": "the-nutshell-s1",
     "lines": [
      "You sealed off your feelings",
      "And with them your heart",
      "So when your heart swells",
      "It blows you apart"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "the-nutshell-s2",
     "lines": [
      "But you have forgotten",
      "That you are the child",
      "Who wants to be special",
      "And aches to run wild"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "the-nutshell-s3",
     "lines": [
      "**This world is a prison**",
      "**For those who accept it**",
      "**Like a room full of doors**",
      "**With no clearly marked exit**"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "the-nutshell-s4",
     "lines": [
      "And you became trapped",
      "In your room full of doors",
      "For you simply did what",
      "Had been done there before"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "the-nutshell-s5",
     "lines": [
      "You learned that the room",
      "Was where you were held",
      "To the whim of the makers",
      "Like a nut in a shell"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "the-nutshell-s6",
     "lines": [
      "But the pressure was building",
      "Inside your cocoon",
      "As the heat of frustration",
      "Came hard and too soon"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "the-nutshell-s7",
     "lines": [
      "You bounced off the walls",
      "In your room full of doors",
      "You bounced off the ceiling",
      "And you bounced off the floor"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "the-nutshell-s8",
     "lines": [
      "In your room full of doors",
      "Where your choices abound",
      "They had you convinced",
      "That your nutshell was sound"
     ]
    },
    {
     "id": "the-nutshell-s9",
     "lines": [
      "But you’re not a walnut",
      "All content in your shell",
      "You’re a kernel of popcorn",
      "You explode like all hell"
     ]
    }
   ]
  }
 ]
}
